VA - Vulnerability Assessment
 tools:
    Nessus or Teneble.io
    OpenVAS has community version which is greenbone scanner

CVSS - Common Vulnerability Scoring System

  0.0 - 0.0  None
  0.1 - 3.9  Low
  4.0 - 6.9  Medium
  7.0 - 8.9  High
  9.0 - 10.0  Critical
  
  

AV - Attack Vector
  N - network
  P - physical
  L - local

CVE - common vulnerabilties and exposures 
  the vulnerability researcher's name is attached to it

NVD - National Vulnerability Database
  Government stuff - basically same















